                  <span class="c00">If you can use the electricity that was saved to <i>pump</i> heat then that&#x27;ll be more efficient.<p>If the only alternative usage is putting the energy into a <i>different</i> hot metal filament, then it might be more of a tossup, depending on how focused the light-bulb&#x27;s emanations are onto the things you actually want warmed.<p><a href="http:&#x2F;&#x2F;scienceline.ucsb.edu&#x2F;getkey.php?key=4006" rel="nofollow">http:&#x2F;&#x2F;scienceline.ucsb.edu&#x2F;getkey.php?key=4006</a><span>
