                  <span class="c00">It probably wasn&#x27;t sagging that killed it. Over time those elements will develop hot spots and eventually the hot spot fails spectacularly spewing sparks and plasma from the failure. It&#x27;s kind of similar to a plasma cutter for a second as there&#x27;s the small arc in the element which ionizes the gas and it blows it out from the element and if it hits something grounded I can totally see it punching a hole through sheet metal.<p><a href="https:&#x2F;&#x2F;youtu.be&#x2F;EC_6urfu5UI?t=7m40s" rel="nofollow">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;youtu.be&#x2F;EC_6urfu5UI?t=7m40s</a><span>
